      "short_description": "Automates Red Hat OpenShift VPC cluster deployment on IBM Cloud, offering full configurability and flexibility for diverse workloads.",
      "long_description": "The Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform on VPC provides the tools to deploy a Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform cluster in a single Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) network. The VPC is a multi-zoned, multi-subnet implementation that keeps your VPC secure and highly available.\n",
      "offering_docs_url": "https://github.com/terraform-ibm-modules/terraform-ibm-base-ocp-vpc/blob/main/README.md",
      "offering_icon_url": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/terraform-ibm-modules/terraform-ibm-base-ocp-vpc/main/images/ocp_icon.svg",
      "provider_name": "IBM",
      "features": [
        {
          "title": "Red Hat OpenShift Cluster",
          "description": "Create and configures a [Red Hat OpenShift VPC cluster](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/openshift) on IBM Cloud."
        },
        {
          "title": "Worker pools",
          "description": "Creates worker pools through which you can group and manage [worker nodes](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/openshift?topic=openshift-add-workers-vpc) with similar configurations, such as compute resources and availability zones."
        },
        {
          "title": "Container Subnets",
          "description": "Configures the [subnets](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/openshift?topic=openshift-vpc-subnets) for the cluster to deploy the worker nodes in."
        },
        {
          "title": "Access Endpoints",
          "description": "Configures [private and public endpoints](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/openshift?topic=openshift-access_cluster) for the cluster."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ingress",
          "description": "Configures the [ingress](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/openshift?topic=openshift-ingress-configure) controller for the cluster, responsible for routing external traffic to the appropriate services within the cluster."
        },
        {
          "title": "Object Storage",
          "description": "Creates and configures an [Object Storage bucket](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/openshift?topic=openshift-storage-cos-understand) required for pods which need persistent volumes and also acts as OpenShift internal registry storage."
        },
        {
          "title": "Key Management Services Encryption",
          "description": "Enables [encryption](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/openshift?topic=openshift-encryption-secrets) of the Kubernetes Secrets and COS bucket using either a newly created key or an existing one."
        }
      ],
      "support_details": "This product is in the community registry, as such support is handled through the originated repo. If you experience issues, please open an issue in the repository [here](https://github.com/terraform-ibm-modules/terraform-ibm-base-ocp-vpc/issues). Please note this product is not supported via the IBM Cloud Support Center.",
